Olesno County ( ) is a unit of territorial administration and local government ( powiat ) in Opole Voivodeship , south - western Poland .
It came into being on January 1 , 1999 , as a result of the Polish local government reforms passed in 1998 .
Its administrative seat and largest town is Olesno , which lies north - east of the regional capital Opole .
The county contains three other towns : Praszka , north of Olesno , Dobrodzień , south of Olesno , and Gorzów Śląski , north of Olesno .
The county covers an area of .
As of 2006 its total population is 68,269 , out of which the population of Olesno is 10,106 , that of Praszka is 8,230 , that of Dobrodzień is 4,168 , that of Gorzów Śląski is 2,606 , and the rural population is 43,159 .
